headline: 1 Bedroom Kitsilano Heritage Suite
thumbnailCaption: Cozy living room with gas fireplace

ownersListingProfile.aboutYou: We are and active and adventuring couple that loves to get outdoors and take advantage of all Vancouver has to offer, including backcountry skiing, mountain biking and running. We are both scientists at UBC, and met working in the lab (ask us about our research on immunotherapy or biofuels from beavers!). Both of us are proudly B.C. born and raised, and Keith grew up nearby in Richmond, so he knows all the ins and outs of this beautiful city. We'd love to help you make sure you love Vancouver as much as we do!
ownersListingProfile.uniqueBenefits:
The location of this unit could not be better - less than 5 blocks from amazing restaurants on West 4th avenue or Broadway, and less than 10 blocks from Kits beach. You can walk everywhere!

Also, living nearby but not in the same building provides the best of both worlds for you - your complete privacy should you desire, but knowing that the hosts are around for anything you might need in a pinch. Having this unit as a dedicated rental means it's always professionally cleaned, and you don't have to worry about encroaching on any personal space :)
ownersListingProfile.whyHere: Georgia has a love of all things vintage, and when we saw this updated suite available less than 5 minutes from our home, we couldn't say no! Georgia has meticulously handpicked all the furnishings to make sure you find the place as homey and cozy as possible.

description:
Beautiful, recently renovated 1 bedroom garden suite in a heritage listed house in Kitsilano. Sleeps 4 comfortably with a queen size bed in the bedroom, and queen size pull out couch, both with memory foam mattresses. Fully equipped kitchen with modern appliances and front loading washer and dryer. Cozy up on the couch near the gas fireplace, or enjoy some beautiful Vancouver afternoon sunshine on the northwest facing patio with gas BBQ. Separate entrance and a walk-out patio makes this a nice private retreat. 

Great location within walking distance to the best shops and restaurants on West 4th or West Broadway, and Kits Beach. Also close to bus routes towards downtown, UBC, Main Street, and Commercial Drive. Easy to get around everywhere.

We live in the area and are happy to offer suggestions for things to do, places to see, and restaurants to eat at. We love the area and think you'll love it too!

reviews.title: " A Gem "
reviews.text:
We stayed in this beautifully appointed heritage  suite for 6 weeks while we visited with our new grandson. Everything about our stay in this rental was wonderful. We found the suite very clean, quiet, safe and in a perfect location.
Just as the owner Keith described, there are many coffee shops, delis, and restaurants a short walk from the apartment. We were one block away from public transit and easy access to UBC, Granville Island and downtown Vancouver. We enjoyed strolling on West Broadway and visiting the Greek delis for a delicious lunch . We bought  fresh fruit from the many markets in this neighbourhood, the best sourdough bread from Cobbs Bakery.
The photos on the HomeAway site don't  show how lovely this suite really is. The kitchen is well equipped, the space is open and inviting  and makes family time most enjoyable. The bedroom has lots of closet space and a very comfortable bed. We loved the large walk- in shower and appreciated the in-floor heating in the bathroom and throughout the whole apartment.
Keith was easy to contact, very welcoming and supportive, and quickly resolved the usual uncertainties of appliances and tv set up. 
Keith and Georgina have made this suite "home". It's a gem of a rental. We will certainly return , highly recommend it to our friends and family, and are very happy to give it a 5 star rating.

reviews.title: Excellent stay and Excellent owner!
reviews.text:
Keith and Georgia,

We thoroughly enjoyed your place! We stayed here for 5 months and it was amazing. The apartment is wonderful and verry cozy. The location in Kitsilano is perfect. It is verry(!) close to public transit so it's easy to go wherever you want. It is also close to the beach but the best thing is that you are close to 4th ave with all the best shops and restaurants! Keith and Georgia also provide you with a guide of the best places. 

The apartment is even better than in the pictures, you will not get disappointed! It is clean and well stocked with all the necessities. The area is safe and the neighbours are verry friendly. 

We definitely recommend you to stay here! 

Thank you for a lovely stay and for making our time in Vancouver truly amazing. We are longing to come back and stay here again!!

Best,
Thilda and Amanda

reviews.title: Keith and Georgia’s suite: two months of true pleasure!!!
reviews.text:
This summer, we rented Keith and Georgia’s suite. 
We were there for two months – between June & July 2016 – and ended up having a delightful time! Our stay was absolutely perfect!!! 
First, the location of the suite is totally fantastic!!!! It is on a very quiet street, in the wonderful neighborhood of Kitsilano. It is a short walk to wonderful beaches, restaurants, stores, and supermarkets. Also, it was an easy commute to downtown, as it is close to several bus stops. 
Second, the listing’s description was exceptionally accurate: the layout, the equipment, and the amenities were on point…and even more beautiful than the pictures! It was as if we were in a true high-end “Hotel Boutique”! The suite was EXTREMELY clean and well maintained. The layout, which offered plenty of space, made it very easy for us to be super comfortable and to keep clean. Plus, the many cupboards/closets, allowed us to stay organized. Moreover, the suite was filled with all the products we needed for the duration of our stay – dishwasher soap, shampoo, laundry soap, etc. – which was perfect. The huge well-furnished kitchen was superb and the bathroom impeccable! 
Fourth, Keith and Georgia provided us with a fantastic customer service! They were super easy to reach, whenever we had inquiries. They would instantly help us, while still respecting our intimacy (they live 4 blocks away) – so it was the best of both worlds! In addition, they provided us with an amazing list of restaurants, shopping area, grocery stores, attractions, and so on, that we really enjoyed! Their hints and recommendations were very useful and accurate!
 We will absolutely go back to Keith & Georgia’s suite, on our next trip to Vancouver. We will strongly recommend it to our friends and relatives. It is a little home away from home! 
Josée & family xxx
